    "comment": "Rationale: An antibody against synaptojanin 1 (then called p145) was used for immunofluorescence in frozen sections of rat brain. Synaptojanin was localized to presynaptic nerve terminals based on co-localization with synapsin. The GO term cytosol was selected because at this level it is not possible to define better localization.. Experimental description: from legend to Fig. 5, \"Localization of p145 and synapsin I by double immunofluorescence in frozen sections of rat brain\".",
